only be used at the end of a word.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-2\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>+Text</code></td>\n				<td>Terms with a leading plus have to be found.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-1\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>-Text</code></td>\n				<td>You can also exclude certain terms from your search by adding a minus sign.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-2\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>Text Text2</code></td>\n				<td>If you just write the words, every possibilitiy will be listed, even if only one of those terms is found. Results containing both terms will be listed topmost.</td></tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-1\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>&gt;Text &lt;Text2</code></td>\n				<td>With the arrow operator you can weight a certain term, which will then be more important within the search results.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-2\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>+Text +(&gt;Text2 &lt;Text3)</code></td>\n				<td>You can also use brackets to make sub-searches. The example will list results including &quot;Text&quot; and &quot;Text2&quot; or &quot;Text&quot; and &quot;Text3&quot;. The terms called first will have a greater importance.</td>\n			</tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-1\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>+Text ~Text2</code></td>\n				<td>The tilde allows you to negate the priority. Results including &quot;Text&quot; and &quot;Text2&quot; will not have a lower priority if &quot;Text2&quot; is not included.</td></tr>\n			<tr class=\"container-2\">\n				<td style=\"white-space: nowrap\"><code>&quot;Text Text2&quot;</code></td>\n				<td>The double quotemark allows you to highlight certain word groups. The search-results will then only include results where the whole word-group appears. &quot;Text, Text2&quot; for example will not be found, because there is a comma in between, which was not entered as phrase.</td>\n			</tr>\n		</tbody>\n	</table>\n</div>\n<p>You can also search for an author and limit the time frame of the search results. Specify also the area to be searched.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,21),(6679,3,'wcf.search.author','Search by author',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6680,3,'wcf.search.error.noMatches','There are no results for your search &quot;{$query}&quot;.',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6681,3,'wcf.search.error.user.noMatches','There are no results from this author.',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6682,3,'wcf.search.general','General search terms',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6683,3,'wcf.search.period','In time period',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6684,3,'wcf.search.period.end','until:',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6685,3,'wcf.search.period.start','from:',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6686,3,'wcf.search.query','Search by key words',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6687,3,'wcf.search.query.description','Enter one or more terms. One term has to contain at least four characters.{if MODULE_HELP} All search possibilities you can find within <a href=\"index.php?page=Help&amp;item=search{@SID_ARG_2ND}\">the help</a>.{/if}',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6688,3,'wcf.search.results','Search results',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6689,3,'wcf.search.results.change','Change search',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6690,3,'wcf.search.results.description','Search results {#$startIndex}-{#$endIndex} of {#$items}{if $query} for &quot;<strong>{$query}</strong>&quot;{/if}.{if $items == 1000} There are even more results, please redefine your search.{/if}{if $highlight}<br />These search terms are highlighted: <span class=\"highlight\">{$highlight}</span>{/if}',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6691,3,'wcf.search.results.display','Display',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6692,3,'wcf.search.results.location','found in:',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6693,3,'wcf.search.sortBy','Sort by',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6694,3,'wcf.search.sortBy.author','Author',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6695,3,'wcf.search.sortBy.creationDate','Date',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6696,3,'wcf.search.sortBy.relevance','Relevance',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6697,3,'wcf.search.sortBy.subject','Subject',0,NULL,0,47,21),(6698,3,'wcf.search.subjectOnly','Onl