class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"{@RELATIVE_WCF_DIR}images/help/helpMessageQuote1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Quote text parts</span></p>\n<p>You can quote messages or content of other users with the help of the quote functions. All messages that can be quoted have a quote button. A click on that button opens a menu with several options:</p>\n<ul>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Quote directly</h5>\n				<p>The complete message will be quoted if you doubleclick the quote button or select the related entry in the quote menu.</p>\n			</li>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Mark to quote</h5>\n				<p>If you want to quote multiple complete messages you can select those with the quote menu.</p>\n			</li>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Quote part of a text directly</h5>\n				<p>If you select a part of a text you can quote it directly. Please note that headlines cannot be quoted!</p>\n			</li>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Quote multiple parts of text</h5>\n				<p>For more detailed quoting, you may want to quote only specific parts of one or several messages. You can achieve that by marking text parts with your mouse and select them for quoting in the quote menu one after another. The selected text parts will be saved so you can use them when writing a new text. You can see a quote count in the buttons of the messages you have taken your quotes from.</p>\n			</li>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Quote paragraphs directly / mark to quote</h5>\n				<p>Do you want to quote the paragraphs of a text you need to choose this option. Each paragraph will be generated into one quote. You can also save the quotes for a later use. In this case you need to select the option &quot;mark to quote&quot;</p>\n			</li>\n		</ul>\n<p>The selected quotes will be saved temporarily so you can first save all quotes and include them later when writing your text. You can find a quote tab below the editor that contains all saved quotes. If you include a quote into your text the quote will be marked to delete. If you post your text the quote will be deleted from your storage. If you want to keep the quote you need to unselect the quote first. Please note that quotes will be only saved for the time of your current session. They are not saved permanently.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,24),(6982,3,'wcf.multiQuote.button.quote','Quote',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6983,3,'wcf.multiQuote.button.quoteMultiple','\"Quote\" + (objectValue.quotes > 0 ? \" (\"+objectValue.quotes+\")\" : \"\")',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6984,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.insertQuote','Insert quote',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6985,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.markParagraphToQuote','Quote selected paragraph',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6986,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.markParagraphsToQuote','Quote paragraphs',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6987,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.markTextToQuote','Quote selected text',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6988,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.markToQuote','Select message to quote',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6989,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.noQuotes','No quotes have been saved.',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6990,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.quoteDirectly','Quote message directly',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6991,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.quoteParagraphDirectly','Quote selected paragraph directly',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6992,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.quoteParagraphsDirectly','Quote paragraphs directly',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6993,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.quoteTextDirectly','Quote selected text directly',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6994,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.removeQuote','Remove quote',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6995,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.removeQuotes','Remove selected quotes',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6996,3,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.selectedQuotes','(count > 1 ? \"The selected quotes\" : \"The selected quote\") + \" will be deleted after submitting the form.\"',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6997,3,'wcf.multiQuote.title','Quotes',0,NULL,0,50,24),(6998,4,'wcf.help.item.message.quote','Quotes',0,NULL,0,24,24),(6999,4,'wcf.help.item.message.quote.description','<p class=\"helpImage border container-4\"><img src=\"{@RELATIVE_WCF_DIR}images/help/helpMessageQuote1.png\" alt=\"\" /><span class=\"smallFont light\">Quote text parts</span></p>\n<p>You can quote messages or content of other users with the help of the quote functions. All messages that can be quoted have a quote button. A click on that button opens a menu with several options:</p>\n<ul>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Quote directly</h5>\n				<p>The complete message will be quoted if you doubleclick the quote button or select the related entry in the quote menu.</p>\n			</li>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Mark to quote</h5>\n				<p>If you want to quote multiple complete messages you can select those with the quote menu.</p>\n			</li>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Quote part of a text directly</h5>\n				<p>If you select a part of a text you can quote it directly. Please note that headlines cannot be quoted!</p>\n			</li>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Quote multiple parts of text</h5>\n				<p>For more detailed quoting, you may want to quote only specific parts of one or several messages. You can achieve that by marking text parts with your mouse and select them for quoting in the quote menu one after another. The selected text parts will be saved so you can use them when writing a new text. You can see a quote count in the buttons of the messages you have taken your quotes from.</p>\n			</li>\n			<li>\n				<h5>Quote paragraphs directly / mark to quote</h5>\n				<p>Do you want to quote the paragraphs of a text you need to choose this option. Each paragraph will be generated into one quote. You can also save the quotes for a later use. In this case you need to select the option &quot;mark to quote&quot;</p>\n			</li>\n		</ul>\n<p>The selected quotes will be saved temporarily so you can first save all quotes and include them later when writing your text. You can find a quote tab below the editor that contains all saved quotes. If you include a quote into your text the quote will be marked to delete. If you post your text the quote will be deleted from your storage. If you want to keep the quote you need to unselect the quote first. Please note that quotes will be only saved for the time of your current session. They are not saved permanently.</p>',0,NULL,0,24,24),(7000,4,'wcf.multiQuote.button.quote','Quote',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7001,4,'wcf.multiQuote.button.quoteMultiple','\"Quote\" + (objectValue.quotes > 0 ? \" (\"+objectValue.quotes+\")\" : \"\")',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7002,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.insertQuote','Insert quote',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7003,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.markParagraphToQuote','Quote selected paragraph',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7004,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.markParagraphsToQuote','Quote paragraphs',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7005,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.markTextToQuote','Quote selected text',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7006,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.markToQuote','Select message to quote',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7007,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.noQuotes','No quotes have been saved.',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7008,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.quoteDirectly','Quote message directly',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7009,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.quoteParagraphDirectly','Quote selected paragraph directly',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7010,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.quoteParagraphsDirectly','Quote paragraphs directly',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7011,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.quoteTextDirectly','Quote selected text directly',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7012,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.removeQuote','Remove quote',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7013,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.removeQuotes','Remove selected quotes',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7014,4,'wcf.multiQuote.quote.selectedQuotes','(count > 1 ? \"The selected quotes\" : \"The selected quote\") + \" will be deleted after submitting the form.\"',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7015,4,'wcf.multiQuote.title','Quotes',0,NULL,0,50,24),(7016,2,'wcf.acp.group.option.admin.user.canPMUser','Kann private Nachrichten versenden',0,NULL,0,3,25),(7017,2,'wcf.acp.group.option.admin.user.canPMUser.description','Mitglieder dieser Benutzergruppe knnen private Nachrichten ber die Administrationsoberflche versenden.',0,NULL,0,3,25),(7018,2,'wcf.acp.group.option.category.user.pm','Private Nachrichten',0,NULL,0,3,25),(7019,2,'wcf.acp.group.opt